      "content": "that's interesting. so if you look at the research regarding those biological factors like testosterone or those evolutionary parenting styles, do these studies suggest that these traits are actually inherent to those specific racial groups, or are they just more prevalent in those groups due to environmental pressure? basically, is there a consensus in the literature on whether these are fixed traits?",
